documentation.text:
@dev
 | The Trust Anchor Extra Data [Unique] reference contract
 | This contract is an example of the type of parameters most useful in a Regulatory/Onboarding/Verification context. A very malleable construction of variables is used, with:
 | a) a mapping of hashes (for lookups on various databases) with a string name for human readability.
 | b) a mapping of ip endpoints (for the transfer of sensitive documents) with a string name for human readability.
 | c) a mapping of 256-bit numeric identifiers (for various indexing purposes) with a string name for human readability.
 | d) a string for public metadata.

@dev Event for setting Public Metadata

 @return result trust anchor manager address

setTrustAnchorDataRetrievalEndpoint(stri.details: Checks whether a specific Trust Anchor has "generic" extraData associated to it with a specific endpoint name, updates if necessary, and returns the status. Sets the endpoint to "enabled" status if it's being set for the first time.

returns.result: | 0: trust anchor is not verified    | 1: endpoint set for the first time    | 2: endpoint updated

setTrustAnchorDataRetrievalEndpointIsEna.details: Checks whether a specific Trust Anchor has "generic" extraData associated to it with a specific endpoint name, and updates the isEnabled if it already exists, and returns the status.

returns.result: | 0: trust anchor is not verified    | 1: endpoint does not exist    | 2: endpoint's enabled status updated
